---
import "../styles/main.css"
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro"
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro"
import ThemeInit from "../components/ThemeInit.astro"
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="scroll-smooth">
<head><meta charset="UTF-8" /><ThemeInit /><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
<title>Learn Spanish with Flashcards - Free App with Spaced Repetition</title>
<meta name="description" content="Learn Spanish vocabulary with free flashcards featuring TTS pronunciation and FSRS spaced repetition. Start with our Spanish 101 deck. No account required." />
<link rel="canonical" href="https://fluentcards.org/learn-spanish/" />
<meta property="og:title" content="Learn Spanish with Flashcards - Free App" />
<meta property="og:description" content="Free Spanish flashcard app with TTS pronunciation and spaced repetition." />
<meta property="og:url" content="https://fluentcards.org/learn-spanish/" />
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
<script type="application/ld+json">{ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "WebPage", "name": "Learn Spanish with Flashcards", "url": "https://fluentcards.org/learn-spanish/" }</script>
<script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-4482389932723468" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>
<body class="font-sans text-slate-700 bg-white dark:bg-surface-dark dark:text-slate-400 antialiased overflow-x-hidden">
<Nav currentPath="/learn-spanish/" />
<main class="pt-32 pb-16 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center reveal-up">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Learn Spanish with Flashcards</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Master Spanish vocabulary with smart flashcards featuring TTS pronunciation, FSRS spaced repetition, and a free Spanish 101 deck. No account needed, works in your browser.</p>
    <a href="/app/" class="mt-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-primary text-white px-8 py-3.5 rounded-xl font-bold shadow-lg shadow-primary/25 hover:shadow-xl transition-all">Start Learning Spanish Free</a>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-16 space-y-8">
    <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-surface-card rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 reveal-up">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 mb-3">Spanish 101 Deck</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">FluentCards includes a free Spanish 101 deck with 35 essential vocabulary words covering greetings, common verbs, numbers, and everyday phrases. Each card includes the Spanish word, English translation, and TTS audio for correct pronunciation. The deck is designed for absolute beginners who want to start speaking Spanish immediately. Clone the deck in one click and begin studying without any setup or account creation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-surface-card rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 reveal-up delay-1">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 mb-3">Spanish TTS Pronunciation</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Spanish pronunciation is relatively straightforward for English speakers, but key sounds like the rolled R and the distinction between B and V require practice. FluentCards uses Microsoft Edge TTS to provide natural Spanish pronunciation for every card. You can choose between Castilian and Latin American accents. Use the TTS feature to hear vocabulary words and full sentences pronounced correctly, and practice shadowing by repeating aloud at the same speed as the audio.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-surface-card rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 reveal-up delay-2">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 mb-3">Spanish Verb Conjugations</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Spanish verbs change form depending on the subject and tense. Flashcards are an excellent tool for drilling conjugations because they allow you to practice one pattern at a time. Create cards showing the infinitive and subject on the front and the conjugated form on the back. Start with present tense, then progress to preterite, imperfect, and future. The FSRS spaced repetition algorithm ensures you review each conjugation pattern at the optimal interval for long-term retention.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-surface-card rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 reveal-up delay-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200 mb-3">Tips for Learning Spanish</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Spanish is one of the most widely spoken languages in the world, with over 500 million native speakers. To learn efficiently, focus on the most common words first. Research shows that knowing the top 1,000 Spanish words covers about 80 percent of everyday conversation. Use FluentCards to build this core vocabulary through spaced repetition, then expand into topic-specific vocabulary related to your interests and goals. Combine flashcard study with real-world practice: listen to Spanish podcasts, watch shows, and find conversation partners online.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

<h2>Getting Started with Spanish</h2>
<p>FluentCards makes it easy to start learning Spanish. When you open the app, you can immediately access the Spanish 101 starter deck with 35 essential vocabulary words. Each card includes the Spanish word, English translation, and TTS audio. The FSRS spaced repetition algorithm automatically schedules your reviews for maximum efficiency. Words you find difficult appear more frequently, while words you know fade into the background.</p>
<h2>Pronunciation and Listening</h2>
<p>FluentCards includes built-in TTS pronunciation that lets you hear each Spanish word spoken naturally. Listen and repeat aloud to practice your pronunciation. Adjust the speech rate from slow to natural speed. Combine flashcard study with real-world exposure to Spanish through podcasts, videos, and conversations for the fastest results.</p>
<h2>Building Your Vocabulary</h2>
<p>Study 15 to 20 minutes daily. Review all due cards and add 5 to 10 new words. At this pace you can learn over 1,000 words in three months. The streak tracker helps maintain momentum, and the FSRS algorithm ensures retention through optimally scheduled reviews.</p>

<p>Spanish 101 starter deck gives you 35 essential Spanish words with English translations and TTS audio. Spanish shares thousands of cognate words with English, giving learners a head start of tens of thousands of words. FluentCards provides all the tools you need to build Spanish vocabulary efficiently through spaced repetition, active recall, and consistent daily practice. The FSRS algorithm adapts to your memory and schedules reviews at optimal intervals. Start with the starter deck and expand with your own cards as you encounter new words in your studies. Whether you are learning for travel, work, or personal enrichment, FluentCards helps you make steady progress toward your Spanish goals.</p><p>Consistent daily practice is the key to language learning success. Study for 15 to 20 minutes each day, complete all due reviews, and add 5 to 10 new vocabulary items. The streak tracker keeps you motivated, and the progress statistics show your improvements over time. With FluentCards, you have a complete language learning system that works on any device, anywhere, without requiring an account or subscription.</p><p>The combination of flashcards, TTS pronunciation, and spaced repetition creates a powerful learning environment that addresses reading comprehension, listening comprehension, and speaking ability simultaneously. By integrating these elements into a single seamless application, FluentCards helps you learn Spanish more efficiently than traditional methods allow.</p>
<p>Spanish is spoken by over 500 million people worldwide, making it the second most spoken native language after Mandarin Chinese. Learning Spanish opens doors to travel, business, and culture across Spain, Latin America, and the United States. Spanish shares thousands of cognate words with English, giving learners a significant head start. FluentCards Spanish 101 deck provides 35 essential words, and as you progress, you can expand your vocabulary with topic-specific decks for travel, business, or literature.</p><p>Spanish verbs have different forms for each person and tense, which can be challenging for English speakers. Create conjugation cards that show the infinitive and subject on the front and the conjugated form on the back. Practice one tense at a time starting with present indicative, then preterite, imperfect, and future. The FSRS algorithm schedules each conjugation pattern at the optimal interval for retention, ensuring you master Spanish verb forms efficiently.</p>
<p>Spanish verb conjugation is one of the most important aspects of the language to master. Unlike English, where verb forms change only slightly, Spanish has distinct endings for each person and tense. The most effective way to learn conjugations is through spaced repetition practice with targeted flashcards. Create cards that show the infinitive and subject pronoun on the front with the conjugated form on the back. Practice one tense at a time, starting with present indicative, then preterite, imperfect, future, and conditional. The FSRS algorithm ensures you review each conjugation at the optimal interval for long-term retention.</p>
<p>FluentCards provides all the tools you need for effective language learning: FSRS spaced repetition, TTS pronunciation in over twenty languages, furigana for Japanese, AI-powered mnemonics, detailed progress tracking, and a community marketplace for sharing decks. All features are completely free with no account required. Start learning today by visiting the app and choosing a starter deck for your target language. The combination of scientifically optimized scheduling, active recall practice, and consistent daily study creates the most efficient path to language fluency available. Your future fluent self will thank you for starting today.</p>
</main>
<Footer />
<script>const o=new IntersectionObserver(e=>{e.forEach(e=>{e.isIntersecting&&e.target.classList.add("visible")})},{threshold:.08});document.querySelectorAll(".reveal-up").forEach(e=>o.observe(e));</script>
</body>
</html>
